426":"1426","1315":"1315","1389":"1389","1400":"1400","1498":"1498","1355":"1355","Kingdom of Thomond, Ireland":"Kingdom of Thomond, Ireland","Ennis Friary, Ennis, Clare, Munster, Ireland":"Ennis, County Clare, Ireland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"O'Brien,","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Dermot, Liam, Brigid, Declan, Donovan, John Patrick, Kieran, Colm, Donal, Brennan, Caitlin.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Briain</b> ‘descendant of <i>Brian</i>’, a personal name probably based on the element <i>bre-</i> ‘hill’, with the transferred sense ‘eminence’, i.e. ‘exalted one’. See also   Bryan  . In Ireland there has also been some confusion with   O'Byrne   (see   Byrne  ).","History: This name is borne in particular by one of the greatest of Irish septs, descendants of Brian Boru, who rose to the high kingship of Ireland in 1002."],"variants":[{"name":"O'Brion","meanings":["Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"O'Bryon","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish William Kevin.","Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"Bryan","meanings":["English and Irish: variant of   Bryant  .","Irish: shortened Anglicized form of <b>Ó Briain</b>, see   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"O'Briant","meanings":["Irish: variant of   O'Brien  , with excrescent <i>-t</i>."]},{"name":"O'Bryant","meanings":["Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"McBrien","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Seamus.","Irish:","Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Briain</b> ‘son of Brian’. See   O'Brien   and   Bryan  ."]},{"name":"O'Brian","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Liam.","Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"O'Bryan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish James Patrick, Padraic.","Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]}]},{"name":"Conchobhar","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Traditional name, probably meaning ‘lover of hounds’; borne by a legendary king of Ulster who lived at the time of Christ."],"variants":[{"name":"Cnochúr","meanings":["Modern Gaelic form of   Conchobhar ."]},{"name":"Conor","meanings":["Anglicized form of   Conchobhar ."]},{"name":"Connor","meanings":["Anglicized form of the Gaelic name Conchobhar . In recent years the name has also become very popular outside Ireland."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Conchobhar macMathghamhna O'Brien, King of Thomond was born about 1360, in Kingdom of Thomond, Ireland, his father, Mathghamhain Maonmhaighe Ó Briain King of Thomond, was 47 and his mother, Úna Ní Conchubhair, Queen of Thomond, was 32. He had at least 1 son. He died on 13 April 1426, in his hometown, at the age of 67."},"et":{"about 1360–13 April 1426":"umbes 1360–13. aprill 1426","1355–1400":"1355–1400","1360–1426":"1360–1426","1382–1498":"1382–1498","1389–Male":"1389–Surnud","1315–Male":"1315–Surnud","1330–1390":"1330–1390","about 1360":"umbes 1360","13 April 1426":"13. aprill 1426","about 1390":"umbes 1390","from 1400 to 1426":"1400 kuni 1426","1330":"1330","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","1390":"1390","1426":"1426","1315":"1315","1389":"1389","1400":"1400","1498":"1498","1355":"1355","Kingdom of Thomond, Ireland":"Kingdom of Thomond, Iirimaa","Ennis Friary, Ennis, Clare, Munster, Ireland":"Ennis, County Clare, Iirimaa"},"fi":{"about 1360–13 April 1426":"noin 1360–13. huhtikuuta 1426","1355–1400":"1355–1400","1360–1426":"1360–1426","1382–1498":"1382–1498","1389–Male":"1389–Kuollut","1315–Male":"1315–Kuollut","1330–1390":"1330–1390","about 1360":"noin 1360","13 April 1426":"13. huhtikuuta 1426","about 1390":"noin 1390","from 1400 to 1426":"vuodesta 1400 vuoteen 1426","1330":"1330","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","1390":"1390","1426":"1426","1315":"1315","1389":"1389","1400":"1400","1498":"1498","1355":"1355","Kingdom of Thomond, Ireland":"Kingdom of Thomond,